{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*
As a customer viewing my plan settings, I want to click a "Learn more about plans" link that opens a modal comparing the Premium and Classic tiers, so that I clearly understand the value proposition (recipe count, exclusive meals, pricing) before switching.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* The modal fetches and displays correct pricing via {{POST /calculate}} and recipe counts (e.g., 64 vs 54 recipes) via {{GET /gw/my-deliveries/menu}}.
** The modal would be setup in [https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-55|https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-55|smart-link] 
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a HelloFresh or migrated Green Chef customer, I want to be able to switch between "Classic" and "Premium" plans within my account settings so that I can easily upgrade or downgrade my subscription tier.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

When the user:

* selects "Premium Plan" -> the user's subscription SKU is updated to the Premium Tier product family (e.g., {{NL-PB-2-2-0}}) via a {{PATCH}} request.
* selects "Classic Plan" -> the user is reverted to the standard product family (e.g., {{NL-CBT19-2-2-0}}).
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Dev Notes:*

# *API Call:* Use {{PATCH /api/subscriptions/{id}}}. Payload example: {{{"subscription": {"product": {"sku": "NL-PB-2-2-0"}}}}}
# *Context:* This component is shared across Web and Native Apps (via Webview). Testing must include changing the browser user agent to iOS/Android to verify the view within the app container
*Reference:* See specific PR linked in PRD for similar logic: [https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|smart-link]  
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

In milestone 0 of our Benelux premium pricing work, we need to show a deprecation notice in the Greenchef NL app. We need to show this notice to inform the users that our GreenChef NL brand will be sunsetted at a given date.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* The banner is created for use as specified in the designs: 
[https://www.figma.com/design/tuClYoEJnghcm7maKCDkWH/BNLX-Premium-Tier?node-id=10942-45624&p=f&t=rwpkXB7GZ7uQmKNh-0|https://www.figma.com/design/tuClYoEJnghcm7maKCDkWH/BNLX-Premium-Tier?node-id=10942-45624&p=f&t=rwpkXB7GZ7uQmKNh-0|smart-link] 
* The banner is gated by the Statsig flag setup in [https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-43|https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-43|smart-link] and [https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-51|https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-51|smart-link] 
* Unit tests are added
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

In milestone 1 of our Benelux premium pricing work, we need to show a deprecation notice in the Greenchef NL app. We need to show this notice to inform the users that our GreenChef NL brand will be sunsetted at a given date. The notice must be hidden behind a Statsig experiment gate to make sure that we don’t make the UI available to the users pre-emptively.

As part of this ticket, we setup this Statsig feature gate.
{panel}



{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* Statsig feature gate is set up and ready for consumption


{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a HelloFresh or migrated Green Chef customer, when I am switching between “Classic” and “Premium”, I want to see the correct prices reflected for either plan type.


!Screenshot 2025-12-16 at 2.48.05 PM.png|width=406,height=996,alt="Screenshot 2025-12-16 at 2.48.05 PM.png"!
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* A dropdown menu is added to the "Plan Settings" / "Manage Subscription" page.
* The dropdown displays two options: "Classic Plan" and "Premium Plan."
* Selecting "Premium Plan" shows the pricing for the premium plan
** Selecting “Classic Plan” shows pricing for the classic plan
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Dev Notes:*

# *Context:* This component is shared across Web and Native Apps (via Webview). Testing must include changing the browser user agent to iOS/Android to verify the view within the app container
*Reference:* See specific PR linked in PRD for similar logic: [https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/pull/58257|smart-link]  
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a developer, I want to remove the Shopify redirection dead code from the FactorForm pages, so that the codebase remains clean, maintainable, and free of unused logic that could cause confusion or performance overhead.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

* The hook for performing the redirect is removed
* The children or components used by the hook for performing the redirect is removed
* The consumption of the redirect hook is removed
* Any new UI (the two step login form) for the redirection is removed
* All of these changes are made in the same commit/PR so that we can revive these changes if necessary
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Dev Notes*

* The cleanup spans across {{whitelabel-web/packages/components/sub-brand-signup/}} and {{whitelabel-web/packages/pages/factorform/}}.

* This removal follows the decision to move away from the Shopify-specific redirection flow for unregistered users in the FactorForm project.

* No functional changes were made to the core login/signup flows; this is strictly a dead code elimination task.
{panel}

