*User Story*

As a prospective Factorform customer who attempts to sign up or log in on the Legacy website ([http://factor75.com/factorform|http://factor75.com/factorform|smart-link] ), if I am not already registered, I must be smoothly and automatically redirected to the corresponding page on the new Shopify website ([https://factor-form-dev.myshopify.com/password|https://factor-form-dev.myshopify.com/password|smart-link]  ) to continue my session there.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

# Email Status Check: After a user enters an email on the Legacy website, a request must be made to the HF gateway endpoint ([https://www.factor75.com/gw/auth/email/status|https://www.factor75.com/gw/auth/email/status]) to check if the email is registered in the legacy Factorform (Factor US, market code: FJ)
# Redirection Trigger: If the check confirms the user is NOT registered ("registered": false), the customer must be redirected to the Shopify website
# Redirection Method: Redirection must be implemented at the website level using the Window.open() method to mitigate potential Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) errors
# Local storage enabled only: The changes must be restricted to a custom local storage flag.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a platform team member, I want to update the SEO metadata (specifically canonical URLs) and footer links on the Legacy Factorform site so that search engines prioritize and index the new Shopify site correctly, and users are directed to the new links.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

# The new canonical URL must be set to the corresponding Shopify website URL, which is defined within the {{factorUSSubBrandConfigOverrides}} configuration
# Override the URLs configured for the website’s footer links (the mapping between a label and a URL) to point to the new Shopify website URLs
# All SEO URL changes must initially be implemented using the {{serverEnv}} hook for environment separation, allowing testing in staging for now.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Dev Notes*

Refer to SEO section in: [https://docs.google.com/document/d/12XXQbzGJCt1xDJzE24eO6_npB21zLA8NT-I0tuq8qpM/edit?usp=sharing|https://docs.google.com/document/d/12XXQbzGJCt1xDJzE24eO6_npB21zLA8NT-I0tuq8qpM/edit?usp=sharing|smart-link] 
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As the engineering team, we want to build a monitoring dashboard in HC so that we can actively track the performance, success rate, and failure rate of the new user segmentation and redirection logic implemented on the Legacy Factorform website ({{factor75.com/factorform}}) immediately after launch.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

# *Total Checks:* The dashboard must display a metric tracking the Total redirect checks triggered
# *Successful Redirects :* The dashboard must display the Percentage of successful redirects (i.e., the percentage of unregistered users on legacy FactorForm correctly sent to Shopify FactorForm)
# *Successful No-Redirects:* The dashboard must display the Successful no-redirects metric (i.e., the percentage of registered users on legacy FactorForm correctly *not* directed to Shopify FactorForm)
# *API Failures:* The dashboard must display a metric tracking API failures (where the email validation endpoint fails to return either registered or unregistered status)
# *Dashboard Creation:* A new board must be created in Honeycomb specifically for monitoring the Legacy website redirection metrics mentioned above.
{panel}

